12:10.645 --> 12:12.156
And some letters she
needs to give to Fidel.

12:12.180 --> 12:13.181
Fidel?

12:13.247 --> 12:15.750
My God, did anyone see you come here?

12:15.817 --> 12:17.351
Why is everybody going to Cuba?

12:17.418 --> 12:18.820
Don't they know it's forbidden?

12:18.887 --> 12:21.590
Man, the police been
following us for days now.

12:21.656 --> 12:22.816
I think we finally lost them.

12:24.292 --> 12:25.760
The police have been following them.

12:25.827 --> 12:27.061
Did you hear this guy?

12:27.128 --> 12:29.063
The police have been
following them, they...

12:29.130 --> 12:32.600
Is something illegal going on here?

12:32.601 --> 12:34.636
That's a very good question you ask.

12:34.703 --> 12:36.270
Oh, look, girls!

12:37.606 --> 12:39.473
Are, are you Black Panthers?

12:39.608 --> 12:41.610
Girls, real Black Panthers!

12:41.643 --> 12:44.412
We are with the Constitutional
Liberation Party.

12:44.478 --> 12:45.680
How exciting.

12:45.747 --> 12:48.216
Which one of you is Abbie Hoffman?

12:48.282 --> 12:50.218
Abbie Hoffman is white.

12:50.284 --> 12:51.620
Are there White Panthers?

12:51.653 --> 12:55.423
In India, Rose Epstein
saw a white tiger.

12:55.489 --> 12:58.159
No, I think you're thinking
of the Detroit Tigers.

12:58.226 --> 12:59.527
Man, what did we get into here?

12:59.628 --> 13:00.829
Where's Lenny?

13:00.895 --> 13:03.197
These people commit criminal acts.

13:03.264 --> 13:05.934
No, these people are freedom fighters.

13:06.000 --> 13:07.736
Right.

13:07.802 --> 13:10.672
You know, Chairman Mao said
that one man's criminal

13:10.739 --> 13:11.916
is another man's freedom fighter.

13:11.940 --> 13:13.474
- That's right.
- Thank you.

13:13.541 --> 13:14.943
Wait, wait, you know what?

13:15.009 --> 13:17.178
I'd like to get you
all something to eat.

13:19.013 --> 13:20.357
All right, everybody,
stay calm all right?

13:20.381 --> 13:21.883
We don't need no fireworks.

13:21.950 --> 13:25.153
No, we should, we should
appear like a normal group.

13:26.054 --> 13:27.388
I don't understand, Ellie.

13:27.455 --> 13:29.166
How can you be serious
about living in Cuba?

13:29.190 --> 13:30.859
Because I love you, and you're gonna

13:30.925 --> 13:32.827
be the father of our child.

13:32.894 --> 13:34.438
Congratulations!

13:34.462 --> 13:35.997
Thank you.

13:36.064 --> 13:38.299
And you said that Havana was romantic.

13:38.366 --> 13:41.770
That there are palm trees and beaches

13:41.836 --> 13:45.674
and anything is possible
if you're in love.

13:45.740 --> 13:47.809
Unless you're in love with someone else.

13:47.876 --> 13:50.912
He's not. He's not in love with me.

13:50.979 --> 13:53.181
He wouldn't last a weekend in Cuba.

13:53.247 --> 13:55.784
He's just in love with what I symbolize.

13:55.850 --> 13:58.319
His inner radical has come
out, which is a step up.

13:58.386 --> 13:59.688
I'm sorry, Allen.

13:59.754 --> 14:02.256
She's that woman on TV.

14:02.323 --> 14:04.158
Oh, my God, that's the escaped fugitive!

14:06.294 --> 14:08.262
For God's sake, Sid, answer the door.

14:08.329 --> 14:12.734
Oh, yes, that's right,
could be the Marx brothers.

14:12.801 --> 14:14.202
We're from the gas company.

14:14.268 --> 14:16.370
We understand there
was a gas leak reported.

14:16.437 --> 14:18.707
No, no, that was a while ago.

14:18.740 --> 14:19.908
It's okay.

14:19.974 --> 14:21.710
- Who are you two?
- Gas company.

14:21.776 --> 14:23.253
How do we know you're
not undercover agents?

14:23.277 --> 14:24.412
For who?

14:24.478 --> 14:25.714
The FBI.

14:25.747 --> 14:27.315
We're here to check a gas leak.

14:27.381 --> 14:28.717
Who are you?

14:28.783 --> 14:30.719
They're members of the Detroit Tigers.

14:30.785 --> 14:32.854
Really? Baseball players.

14:32.921 --> 14:36.224
The gas is, the, the,
the basement's over there.

14:37.792 --> 14:40.061
I need to get to this
spot just right up here.

14:40.128 --> 14:41.830
The roads are not safe.

14:41.896 --> 14:43.140
She's gonna have to get out

14:43.164 --> 14:44.404
in the trunk of somebody's car.

14:44.465 --> 14:45.834
Somebody's gotta drive her.

14:45.900 --> 14:48.636
- You two guys can take her.
- Are you kidding?

14:48.737 --> 14:51.015
We'll be stopped and searched
by every trooper on the highway.

14:51.039 --> 14:52.540
- I'll drive her.
- No, you will not.

14:52.606 --> 14:53.842
You will not!

14:53.908 --> 14:55.744
No one in this house is going to help

14:55.810 --> 14:57.611
a wanted criminal escape.

14:57.746 --> 14:59.890
- Are you crazy?
- No, look, I said I'm gonna take her.

14:59.914 --> 15:01.582
- I'm gonna take her.
- I said no.

15:01.649 --> 15:03.317
Let's go.

15:03.384 --> 15:05.329
If you don't get there on time,
he'll get nervous and leave.

15:05.353 --> 15:06.755
I'll drive you!

15:06.788 --> 15:08.489
You can't, Helen. With your eyesight

15:08.556 --> 15:10.825
and sense of direction,
you'll wind up in Brooklyn.

15:10.892 --> 15:13.194
But she's a sister revolutionary.

15:13.261 --> 15:14.963
Listen, if you miss this plane we can't

15:15.029 --> 15:16.798
set up an escape for another month.

15:16.865 --> 15:19.767
You could wind up stuck
here God knows how long.

15:19.768 --> 15:20.835
I'll take her.

15:20.902 --> 15:22.771
No, yes, I'm gonna take you.

15:22.837 --> 15:24.305
Are you crazy? You'll drive her?

15:24.372 --> 15:26.140
She's not gonna be here another month

15:26.207 --> 15:28.776
because she eats my sturgeon,
she eats my navel oranges.

15:28.777 --> 15:30.311
She's out, I want her out.

15:30.378 --> 15:32.781
Hey, you don't have a gas
line that extends out...

15:32.814 --> 15:34.515
Hey, aren't you the...

15:34.582 --> 15:36.885
You're that escaped criminal
the FBI's looking for.

15:36.951 --> 15:38.820
Okay, you two, up against that wall.

15:38.887 --> 15:40.788
Go up against the wall. You'll be fine.

15:40.789 --> 15:42.156
Just stay against the wall.

15:42.223 --> 15:45.393
Let's go, Lenny. Time's running out.

15:45.459 --> 15:47.528
- Wish me luck.
- Don't want to miss your plane.

15:47.595 --> 15:49.206
I know what you're
thinking. You're thinking

15:49.230 --> 15:52.200
you were never prouder
of me in this moment.

15:52.266 --> 15:55.036
Hand signal, please.
You're a terrible driver.

15:55.103 --> 15:56.871
She's right, she's right.

16:03.644 --> 16:05.313
Okay, get into the trunk.

16:05.379 --> 16:06.714
- What?
- Get into the trunk.

16:06.815 --> 16:08.549
You want me to get in the trunk?

16:08.616 --> 16:10.194
Yeah, unless you want me
to put you under the hood.

16:10.218 --> 16:12.954
- Oh, Jesus Christ.
- Get into the trunk.

16:13.955 --> 16:15.623
Try and get comfortable.

16:15.689 --> 16:17.434
It's a little tight in
there, but you'll make it.

16:17.458 --> 16:18.726
Oh, God.

16:33.674 --> 16:35.877
I need help now, I need help.

16:47.388 --> 16:49.723
Would you have really
gone to Cuba with me?

16:49.858 --> 16:51.325
I said I loved you.

16:51.392 --> 16:53.895
And you do know that,
even after we're married

16:53.962 --> 16:56.130
I still plan to be
very active in helping

16:56.197 --> 16:58.732
our country reach its full potential?

16:58.867 --> 17:01.335
That's fine, but no
more explosions okay?

17:01.402 --> 17:02.871
No, no, no.

17:02.904 --> 17:05.874
Now that I'm going to be a father.

17:05.906 --> 17:07.375
And we can move to San Diego.

17:07.441 --> 17:08.776
Yeah, sure, you know.

17:08.877 --> 17:10.878
As good a place as any.

17:10.944 --> 17:12.880
And you won't get too radical.

17:12.881 --> 17:13.982
Only in bed.

17:14.048 --> 17:16.885
Come here.

17:20.421 --> 17:23.590
- Sorry.
- No, no, I'm fine, I'm fine.

17:37.138 --> 17:40.574
You know how fast you were going?

17:40.641 --> 17:42.911
Let me guess. Too fast, right?

17:42.977 --> 17:45.513
What, are you a wise guy?

17:45.579 --> 17:48.482
Let me see your license.

17:48.549 --> 17:50.184
Jesus.

17:50.251 --> 17:51.619
You're not gonna believe this.

17:51.685 --> 17:53.754
Office, this has never
happened to me before.

17:53.821 --> 17:56.290
I left it on the table in my foyer.

17:56.357 --> 17:58.927
I've never once been
out without my license.

17:58.960 --> 18:02.463
Okay, okay, can I see your registration?

18:13.607 --> 18:15.609
It's, it's not in there.

18:15.676 --> 18:19.948
Okay, step out of the car
please and open your trunk.

18:19.981 --> 18:21.115
The trunk?

18:25.353 --> 18:27.555
The, the, the trunk of my car?

18:27.621 --> 18:29.690
Yeah, where you heading so fast, huh?

18:29.757 --> 18:32.026
I, I, I'm, I gotta catch a plane.

18:32.093 --> 18:33.670
Yeah, well, there's no
airports around here.

18:33.694 --> 18:36.764
Yeah, I was gonna take
a private to the airport.

18:36.830 --> 18:39.967
Well, you know, shouldn't
be driving without a license.

18:39.968 --> 18:41.069
I know, I know.

18:41.135 --> 18:43.771
I've never done that before.

18:43.837 --> 18:46.174
Have I seen you somewhere, huh?

18:46.240 --> 18:47.075
Me?

18:47.141 --> 18:48.076
I don't think so.

18:48.142 --> 18:49.710
You look familiar to me.

18:49.777 --> 18:52.146
Maybe you know me from
my... maybe you read my book.

18:52.213 --> 18:54.082
You know me from my book jacket.

18:54.148 --> 18:55.616
Yeah, who are you?

18:55.683 --> 18:57.218
S. J. Muntzinger.

18:58.186 --> 18:59.988
You're S. J. Muntzinger?

19:00.054 --> 19:01.055
Yeah.

19:01.122 --> 19:03.124
The S. J. Muntzinger?

19:03.191 --> 19:06.427
Yeah, you know my books?

19:06.494 --> 19:09.597
My God, you're, you're,
you're, you're, you're a genius!

19:09.663 --> 19:12.066
Well, you know I, I try.

19:12.133 --> 19:14.035
What are you doing out here?

19:14.102 --> 19:18.106
I thought you, I thought
you lived in Manhattan.

19:18.172 --> 19:21.475
No, no, I'm up here in this area.

19:21.542 --> 19:24.011
Ah, I gotta tell you I loved your book

19:24.012 --> 19:25.546
and my kids did too.

19:25.613 --> 19:27.715
They're the ones who
actually turned me onto it.

19:27.781 --> 19:28.616
It's great!

19:28.682 --> 19:29.682
Oh, well, thank you.

19:29.717 --> 19:30.851
Thank you very much.

19:30.918 --> 19:32.553
A real genius.

19:32.620 --> 19:37.091
Although I have to say, I
thought you'd be much younger.

19:37.158 --> 19:40.194
Well, I, you know, nothing
I can do about that.

19:40.261 --> 19:43.097
I, it's my haircut probably.

19:43.164 --> 19:46.900
Yeah, so this is what
you look like, huh?

19:47.035 --> 19:49.403
Yeah, for better or worse.

19:49.470 --> 19:51.039
Yeah, well, let me ask you a question.

19:51.105 --> 19:52.349
I mean, where do you come up with

19:52.373 --> 19:54.175
a character like Holden Caulfield?

19:54.242 --> 19:56.277
Where does that come from?

19:56.344 --> 19:57.845
What?

19:57.911 --> 19:59.147
And where do the ducks in

19:59.213 --> 20:01.082
Central Park go during the winter?

20:01.149 --> 20:04.885
Where do they go, to the Hamptons?

20:04.952 --> 20:07.521
I gotta tell you, man, it was
a real pleasure to meet you.

20:07.588 --> 20:09.790
You know, I haven't
read a book like yours

20:09.857 --> 20:12.793
and enjoyed it in a long
time and I'm not a big reader.

20:12.860 --> 20:14.228
You know what I mean?

20:14.295 --> 20:15.672
But it's just, the
way you used the words

20:15.696 --> 20:17.698
and then did jokes,
it was just so funny.

20:17.765 --> 20:21.102
Look at that, S. J.
Muntzinger right here huh?

20:21.169 --> 20:23.071
Yes, in person.

20:23.137 --> 20:24.338
Is that you're supposed to be

20:24.405 --> 20:27.675
some sort of a weirdo recluse, huh?

20:27.741 --> 20:31.779
Well, I, you know I
get out now and then to

20:31.845 --> 20:36.484
you know shop for groceries
and, you know, my colonoscopy.

20:36.550 --> 20:38.486
Oh, yeah? I had one of those once.

20:38.552 --> 20:39.887
You know my throat was killing me

20:39.953 --> 20:41.273
and the doctor took it right out.

20:41.322 --> 20:42.866
Hey, look, I'm not
gonna give you a ticket.

20:42.890 --> 20:45.726
Your book gave me so
much pleasure, but, uh...

20:45.793 --> 20:48.662
would you mind giving me an autograph?

20:48.729 --> 20:51.599
Oh, sure, but, yeah, come over here.

20:51.665 --> 20:53.033
- Yeah?
- Yeah, just step...

20:53.101 --> 20:54.735
As a matter of fact,

20:54.802 --> 20:57.171
if you like, what I'll do,
I'll personalize it for you.

20:57.238 --> 20:59.006
Okay yeah, yeah, Trooper Mike.

20:59.073 --> 21:01.109
Trooper Mike.

21:01.142 --> 21:02.143
My good friend.

21:02.210 --> 21:04.112
My good friend.

21:04.178 --> 21:05.189
Who's not giving me a ticket even though

21:05.213 --> 21:06.880
I was driving like a lunatic.

21:06.947 --> 21:09.117
Okay, I can't do it all, Mike.

21:09.150 --> 21:12.120
I'll just say "My good
friend trooper Mike.

21:12.186 --> 21:17.358
"God bless you", and...
"S. J. Muntzinger."

21:17.425 --> 21:19.960
Wow, what a pleasure. I
really, I appreciate it.

21:20.027 --> 21:22.029
It's a real pleasure to meet you.

21:22.130 --> 21:24.132
- Oh, thank you.
- I mean, what a thrill.

21:24.198 --> 21:26.167
Thank you, you too, God bless you, Mike.

21:29.203 --> 21:31.138
What a day.

21:31.139 --> 21:33.174
What an experience.

21:33.241 --> 21:36.910
And we were out of little frankfurters.

21:36.977 --> 21:39.180
Do you think she made it?

21:39.247 --> 21:40.257
Oh, I think we would have heard

21:40.281 --> 21:42.416
if anything happened.

21:42.483 --> 21:45.586
Hopefully she's in Cuba now.

21:45.653 --> 21:48.256
Well, you're not gonna
say you, you miss her?

21:48.322 --> 21:50.224
I, I never liked her.

21:50.291 --> 21:52.159
You know,"beware of fanatics

21:52.160 --> 21:56.163
"no matter how just their cause seems."

21:56.164 --> 21:58.166
Oh, who said that?

21:58.199 --> 22:01.435
That was Chairman Sidney Muntzinger.

22:03.604 --> 22:05.173
Back to real life.

22:05.239 --> 22:07.608
You can go to work on your sitcom now.

22:09.177 --> 22:10.478
Let me ask you a question.

22:10.544 --> 22:13.847
Do you think that it's in me to write

22:13.914 --> 22:16.617
a novel as good as "The
Catcher in the Rye"?

22:18.186 --> 22:19.620
Why do you ask that?

22:19.687 --> 22:21.489
I was just thinking maybe I should dump

22:21.555 --> 22:24.425
this whole idiotic
television series thing

22:24.492 --> 22:28.962
and, you know, give one last
shot to writing the book.

22:29.029 --> 22:30.298
I, I, I...

22:30.364 --> 22:33.234
Hey, I'm not getting any younger.

22:33.301 --> 22:35.202
Well, why not?

22:35.203 --> 22:37.505
You're amusing, and I always said

22:37.571 --> 22:40.007
you could be another Salinger.

